   "source": [
    "# Mamba · Selective State Space Models\n",
    "## Notebook de trabajo · Comparativa con Transformer e híbrido\n",
    "\n",
    "Basado en:\n",
    "- **Mamba: Linear-Time Sequence Modeling with Selective State Spaces** (Gu & Dao, 2023)\n",
    "- Implementación simplificada para enseñanza\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objetivo de la sesión\n",
    "\n",
    "Comparar tres enfoques de modelización secuencial:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **MiniTransformer**: atención global pura (referencia)\n",
    "2. **MiniMamba**: Selective State Spaces (sin atención)\n",
    "3. **HybridMamba**: mezcla de Mamba con atención estratégica\n",
    "\n",
    "Buscamos entender:\n",
    "- Qué son los State Space Models\n",
    "- Cómo funciona la selección de contenido en Mamba\n",
    "- Por qué Mamba escala linealmente\n",
    "- Cuándo merece la pena añadir atención"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports y preparación"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from tqdm.auto import tqdm\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
    "print(f\"Dispositivo: {device}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Dataset: Don Quijote"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ======================================\n",
    "# Descarga y preparación de Don Quijote\n",
    "# ======================================\n",
    "data_path = Path(\"el_quijote.txt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not data_path.exists():\n",
    "    print(\"Descargando Don Quijote...\")\n",
    "    url = \"https://www.gutenberg.org/files/2000/2000-0.txt\"\n",
    "    response = requests.get(url, timeout=30)\n",
    "    response.raise_for_status()\n",
    "    text = response.text\n",
    "    start_marker = \"*** START OF THE PROJECT GUTENBERG\"\n",
    "    end_marker = \"*** END OF THE PROJECT GUTENBERG\"\n",
    "    start_idx = text.find(start_marker) + len(start_marker)\n",
    "    end_idx = text.find(end_marker)\n",
    "    text = text[start_idx:end_idx].strip()\n",
    "    data_path.write_text(text)\n",
    "\n",
    "text = data_path.read_text()\n",
    "print(f\"Longitud del texto: {len(text):,} caracteres\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Tokenización a nivel de carácter\n",
    "chars = sorted(list(set(text)))\n",
    "vocab_size = len(chars)\n",
    "stoi = {ch: i for i, ch in enumerate(chars)}\n",
    "itos = {i: ch for i, ch in enumerate(chars)}\n",
    "\n",
    "data = torch.tensor([stoi[ch] for ch in text], dtype=torch.long)\n",
    "print(f\"Vocabulario: {vocab_size} caracteres\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_batch(batch_size=64, block_size=128, device='cpu'):\n",
    "    ix = torch.randint(len(data) - block_size, (batch_size,))\n",
    "    x = torch.stack([data[i:i+block_size] for i in ix])\n",
    "    y = torch.stack([data[i+1:i+block_size+1] for i in ix])\n",
    "    return x.to(device), y.to(device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Bloques fundamentales\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 State Space Models: la base\n",
    "\n",
    "Un SSM continuo mapea una señal de entrada u(t) a una salida y(t) a través de un estado interno h(t):\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "h'(t) = A·h(t) + B·u(t)   (ecuación de estado)\n",
    "y(t)    = C·h(t) + D·u(t)  (ecuación de salida)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Para secuencias discretas (lo que tenemos):\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "h_t = A_t·h_{t-1} + B_t·u_t\n",
    "y_t  = C_t·h_t + D_t·u_t\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Donde A, B, C, D son **parámetros aprendibles**.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.2 La innovación de Mamba: selección\n",
    "\n",
    "La diferencia clave es que en Mamba, **A, B, C dependen del input**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "B_t = Linear_x(x_t)\n",
    "C_t = Linear_x(x_t)\n",
    "A_t = A_log - pa exp(log dt + exp(log_B))  (parametrización del tiempo de estado)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Esto permite que el modelo **seleccione qué información recordar** basándose en el contenido."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ======================================\n",
    "# BLOQUES\n",
    "# ======================================\n",
    "\n",
    "class RMSNorm(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, d_model, eps=1e-5):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.eps = eps\n",
    "        self.weight = nn.Parameter(torch.ones(d_model))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        output = x * torch.rsqrt(x.pow(2).mean(-1, keepdim=True) + self.eps)\n",
    "        return self.weight * output\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class MambaBlock(nn.Module):\",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Bloque Mamba: Selective State Space Model\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Componentes:\n",
    "    1. Proyección de entrada (x → z, x_inner)\n",
    "    2. Selección SSM (B, C, dt, A)\n",
    "    3. Operaciones de convolución + recurrencia\n",
    "    4. Puerta de salida\n",
    "    \n",
    "    La selección permite al modelo decidir dinámicamente qué的记忆 guardar.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, d_model, d_state=16, d_conv=4, expand=2):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.d_model = d_model\n",
    "        self.d_state = d_state\n",
    "        self.d_inner = int(expand * d_model)\n",
    "        self.d_conv = d_conv\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Proyecciones\n",
    "        self.in_proj = nn.Linear(d_model, self.d_inner * 2, bias=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Convolución 1D para preprocessar\n",
    "        self.conv1d = nn.Conv1d(\n",
    "            in_channels=self.d_inner,\n",
    "            out_channels=self.d_inner,\n",
    "            kernel_size=d_conv,\n",
    "            padding=d_conv - 1,\n",
    "            groups=self.d_inner,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Parámetros SSM (x → B, C, dt)\n",
    "        self.x_proj = nn.Linear(self.d_inner, d_state * 2 + 1, bias=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Parametrización de A (matriz de estado)\n",
    "        self.A_log = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(self.d_inner, d_state))\n",
    "        self.D = nn.Parameter(torch.ones(self.d_inner))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.out_proj = nn.Linear(self.d_inner, d_model, bias=False)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        b, l, d = x.shape\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Split: primera mitad = z (gate), segunda = x_inner\n",
    "        xz = self.in_proj(x)\n",
    "        x_inner, z = xz.chunk(2, dim=-1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Convolución local\n",
    "        x_inner = x_inner.transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "        x_inner = self.conv1d(x_inner)[:, :, :l]\n",
    "        x_inner = x_inner.transpose(1, 2)\n",
    "        x_inner = F.silu(x_inner)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Proyecciones para B, C, dt\n",
    "        x_decay = self.x_proj(x_inner)\n",
    "        B, C, dt = x_decay.split([self.d_state, self.d_state, 1], dim=-1)\n",
    "        dt = F.softplus(dt)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # A discretizado\n",
    "        A = -torch.exp(self.A_log.float())\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # SSM scan (versión simplificada - ver nota abajo)\n",
    "        y = self.ssm_select(x_inner, dt, A, B, C)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Puerta y salida\n",
    "        y = y * torch.sigmoid(z)\n",
    "        y = y + x * torch.sigmoid(self.D)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return self.out_proj(y)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def ssm_select(self, x, dt, A, B, C):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        SSM con selección de contenido.\n",
    "        \n",
    "        Esta es una versión simplificada del scan. En producción\n",
    "        se usa el algoritmo paralelo de Mamba con hardware-aware optimizations.\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        b, l, d_inner = x.shape\n",
    "        d_state = self.d_state\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Inicializar estado\n",
    "        h = torch.zeros(b, d_inner, d_state, device=x.device, dtype=x.dtype)\n",
    "        outputs = []\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for i in range(l):\n",
    "            # Discretización: h = dt * (A @ h_prev) + dt * (B @ x)\n",
    "            # dt[i] actúa como \"tiempo de retención\"\n",
    "            dti = dt[:, i, :]\n",
    "            Bi = B[:, i, :]\n",
    "            Ci = C[:, i, :]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Estado nuevo: mezcla selectiva\n",
    "            h_new = dti.unsqueeze(-1) * (A.unsqueeze(0) * h + (Bi.unsqueeze(1) * x[:, i, :].unsqueeze(-1)))\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Salida: y = C @ h\n",
    "            y_i = (Ci.unsqueeze(1) * h_new).sum(-1)\n",
    "            outputs.append(y_i)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            h = h_new\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return torch.stack(outputs, dim=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class AttentionBlock(nn.Module):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Bloque de atención multi-cabeza (referencia Transformer).\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def __init__(self, d_model, n_heads):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.attn = nn.MultiheadAttention(d_model, n_heads, batch_first=True)\n",
    "        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(d_model)\n",
    "        self.ff = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Linear(d_model, 4 * d_model),\n",
    "            nn.GELU(),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(4 * d_model, d_model)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        attn_out, _ = self.attn(x, x, x)\n",
    "        x = self.norm(x + attn_out)\n",
    "        x = self.norm(x + self.ff(x))\n",
    "        return x"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Modelos completos\n",
    "\n",
    "Estructura:\n",
    "- **MiniTransformer**: 6 capas de atención\n",
    "- **MiniMamba**: 12 capas Mamba\n",
    "- **HybridMamba**: atención cada 3 capas, Mamba el resto"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ======================================\n",
    "# MODELOS\n",
    "# ======================================\n",
    "\n",
    "class MiniTransformer(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, vocab_size, d_model=128, n_heads=4, n_layers=6):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.embed = nn.Embedding(vocab_size, d_model)\n",
    "        self.pos_embed = nn.Parameter(torch.randn(1, 512, d_model) * 0.02)\n",
    "        self.layers = nn.ModuleList([AttentionBlock(d_model, n_heads) for _ in range(n_layers)])\n",
    "        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(d_model)\n",
    "        self.head = nn.Linear(d_model, vocab_size)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        b, l = x.shape\n",
    "        x = self.embed(x) + self.pos_embed[:, :l, :]\n",
    "        for layer in self.layers:\n",
    "            x = layer(x)\n",
    "        return self.head(self.norm(x))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class MiniMamba(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, vocab_size, d_model=128, n_layers=12, **mamba_kwargs):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.embed = nn.Embedding(vocab_size, d_model)\n",
    "        self.layers = nn.ModuleList([MambaBlock(d_model, **mamba_kwargs) for _ in range(n_layers)])\n",
    "        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(d_model)\n",
    "        self.head = nn.Linear(d_model, vocab_size)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        x = self.embed(x)\n",
    "        for layer in self.layers:\n",
    "            x = layer(x)\n",
    "        return self.head(self.norm(x))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class HybridMamba(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, vocab_size, d_model=128, n_layers=12, **mamba_kwargs):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.embed = nn.Embedding(vocab_size, d_model)\n",
    "        layers = []\n",
    "        for i in range(n_layers):\n",
    "            if i % 3 == 0:\n",
    "                layers.append(AttentionBlock(d_model, n_heads=4))\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                layers.append(MambaBlock(d_model, **mamba_kwargs))\n",
    "        self.layers = nn.ModuleList(layers)\n",
    "        self.norm = nn.LayerNorm(d_model)\n",
    "        self.head = nn.Linear(d_model, vocab_size)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        x = self.embed(x)\n",
    "        for layer in self.layers:\n",
    "            x = layer(x)\n",
    "        return self.head(self.norm(x))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Entrenamiento y generación"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ======================================\n",
    "# ENTRENAMIENTO\n",
    "# ======================================\n",
    "\n",
    "def train_and_generate(model, name, epochs=8, batch_size=64, block_size=128, \n",
    "                       lr=4e-4, device='cuda', temperature=0.8, save_dir=\"models_mamba\"):\n",
    "    import os\n",
    "    os.makedirs(save_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    model = model.to(device)\n",
    "    optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=lr, weight_decay=0.1)\n",
    "    scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.CosineAnnealingLR(optimizer, T_max=epochs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n=== Entrenando {name} ===\")\n",
    "    losses = []\n",
    "    best_loss = float('inf')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for epoch in range(epochs):\n",
    "        model.train()\n",
    "        total_loss = 0\n",
    "        steps = 80\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for _ in tqdm(range(steps), desc=f\"Epoch {epoch+1}/{epochs}\"):\n",
    "            x, y = get_batch(batch_size, block_size, device)\n",
    "            logits = model(x)\n",
    "            loss = F.cross_entropy(logits.view(-1, vocab_size), y.view(-1))\n",
    "            optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "            loss.backward()\n",
    "            torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), 1.0)\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\n",
    "            total_loss += loss.item()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        scheduler.step()\n",
    "        avg_loss = total_loss / steps\n",
    "        losses.append(avg_loss)\n",
    "        print(f\"Epoch {epoch+1:2d} | Loss: {avg_loss:.4f} | LR: {scheduler.get_last_lr()[0]:.2e}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if avg_loss < best_loss:\n",
    "            best_loss = avg_loss\n",
    "            torch.save(model.state_dict(), f\"{save_dir}/{name.replace(' ', '_')}_best.pt\")\n",
    "            print(f\"  → Mejor modelo (loss {best_loss:.4f})\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "    plt.plot(range(1, epochs+1), losses, marker='o', label=name)\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"Curva de pérdida - {name}\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Época\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Pérdida (cross-entropy)\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(True)\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\nGenerando texto con temperatura = {temperature}...\")\n",
    "    model.eval()\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        context = torch.tensor([stoi[' ']], dtype=torch.long, device=device).unsqueeze(0)\n",
    "        generated = []\n",
    "        for _ in range(400):\n",
    "            logits = model(context)\n",
    "            logits = logits[:, -1, :] / temperature\n",
    "            probs = F.softmax(logits, dim=-1)\n",
    "            next_idx = torch.multinomial(probs, num_samples=1)\n",
    "            context = torch.cat([context, next_idx], dim=1)\n",
    "            generated.append(itos[next_idx.item()])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"\\n--- Texto generado por {name} (temp={temperature}) ---\")\n",
    "        print(''.join(generated))\n",
    "        print(\"-\" * 70)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Ejecución"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ======================================\n",
    "# EJECUTAR COMPARACIÓN\n",
    "# ======================================\n",
    "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
    "    device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Dispositivo: {device}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    d_model = 128\n",
    "    save_dir = \"saved_models_mamba\"\n",
    "    TEMPERATURE = 0.85\n",
    "    EPOCHS = 8\n",
    "    \n",
    "    models = [\n",
    "        (\"MiniTransformer\", MiniTransformer(vocab_size, d_model, n_heads=4, n_layers=6)),\n",
    "        (\"Pure Mamba\", MiniMamba(vocab_size, d_model, n_layers=12)),\n",
    "        (\"Hybrid Mamba\", HybridMamba(vocab_size, d_model, n_layers=12))\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for name, model in models:\n",
    "        train_and_generate(\n",
    "            model, \n",
    "            name, \n",
    "            epochs=EPOCHS, \n",
    "            device=device, \n",
    "            temperature=TEMPERATURE,\n",
    "            save_dir=save_dir\n",
    "        )"
   ]
  }
